<topic id="folding-in-css-stylesheets">
  <title>Folding in CSS Stylesheets</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>CSS stylesheets<indexterm>Folding</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p id="p_m32_cgk_54b">In a large CSS stylesheet document, some styles can be collapsed so that
      only the styles that are needed remain in focus. The same folding features available for XML
      documents are also available in CSS stylesheets.<note id="note_n32_cgk_54b"><ph
          conkeyref="reusables-editing-documents/selecting-blocks"/></note></p>
  </body>
